args: Hell yes! It's finally time for a breather!\nI tell ya, comin' back home to kick yer\nfeet up does a man a world'a good.
I understand what you mean, Ranzal,\neven though I have only been staying\nat the Halidom for a small while now.
It seems like you're fitting in well\nwith everyone here, Sharena.
I certainly am! The people here are all\nlovely, and I hope to become friends\nwith them all!
You see things a little differently\nfrom Alfonse, don't you?
Well, I always got the impression that he\ndrew a fine line between faith in one's\nallies and actual friendship.
Yes, my brother did often remind me not\nto get too attached to our Heroes.
But he has his ways, and I have mine.

Bwa ha ha! If yer lookin' to become
friends, it's way too late for that.
Once ya fight alongside someone,
yer ALREADY they're friend!
Aaaargh! Knock it off, Sarisse!\nI'm sorry! Forgive meee!
Goodness, that was quite the racket!\nAre you all right, Luca?
Ha! Just business as usual around here.\nDon't worry about it.
Er, but it appears that Luca's eyes\nhave rolled back into his head.
Ha ha...ha? Yeah, maybe I whacked him\njust a little too hard there...
Ranzal and I will carry him to his room.
Ranzal said this was ＂business as usual,＂\nSarisse. Are you and Luca often like this?
Yeah, I guess you could say that.\nHe does something boneheaded,\nthen I give him the business.
But that's what brothers and sisters do.\nI mean, don't you and Alfonse ever fight?

In that case, we should have a brother
swap. You can spend your days getting
mad at Lunkhead Luca, and I can float
around agreeing with Mr. Perfect.
In truth, I'm jealous of your relationship.\nI've never really connected with my\nbrother in that fashion.
Sharena, this is NOT a good thing!\nTrust me, it's waaay better to have a\ngrown-up older brother like Alfonse.
But Luca is so good-humored\nand considerate of you.
And Alfonse is serious and grown up!\nHe HAS to be the better brother!
It's true that my brother is kind and hard-\nworking, and always looking out for me as\nwe work together in the Order of Heroes...
...But he's also a rather chronic worrier.\nYou might even say he doesn't trust me.
That dope ignores my feelings, does and\nsays whatever he wants, then takes off\non his own and makes me worry!
Grrnghf! I-I give up! I was wrong!\nM-mercy!
Ho, Sarisse! I'm glad you're safe.\nI was so worried.
Stay the hell away from my sister! Haaah!
Luca's a bonehead... And brash...\nAnd sort of stupid... And a child...\nBut sometimes he can be pretty cool.
But just sometimes! Like, I'm talking\nmega ultra TURBO rare occasions.\nUsually he's just a big ol' meathead.
Heh. It seems you two are actually\nquite close after all.
Man, now you've got me all worried\nabout how hard I whacked him...
I'm sure you'll patch things up in no time.\nAfter all, he's your older brother.
Perhaps you can bake him some treats\nby way of apology.
My brother always loves it when I bring\nhim homemade treats, and I'm sure Luca\nwould as well.

Luca was the one who messed up,
but I DO feel like I overdid it a little...
So yeah, it might actually be good
for me to apologize somehow.
But wouldn't he think it's weird for me\nto suddenly do something like that?
If you poured your heart into them,\nI'm sure he would love it.
Yeah, maybe. But I ain't exactly Cleo\nwhen it comes to the ol' kitchen.
Well, I'm something of an amateur baker.\nPerhaps we can make them together?
Oh, it's so good to be making\nreal friends here!
You can double that feeling on my end!
Well then, let's get over to the kitchen\nand see about those treats.
